The paper deals with the algebraic structure and enumeration of Boolean functions, which are topics that are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of algebraic methods suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), while the focus on computational systems biology suggests that it may belong to cs.SI (Systems and Control). The study of Boolean networks and functions is also relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
